This paper is likely to belong to the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-category as it proposes a benchmark for distributed stream processing systems. It also involves processing large volumes of data in real-time, which is a common theme in this sub-category. 

The paper also deals with data management and processing, which suggests that it could belong to the Databases (cs.DB) sub-category. 

As the Aadhaar biometric database is a critical infrastructure, the paper may also belong to the Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) sub-category, as it may involve security and privacy concerns. 

The paper proposes a benchmark for eGovernance applications, which suggests that it could belong to the Software Engineering (cs.SE) sub-category. 

Finally, as the Aadhaar biometric database is a national identity infrastructure, the paper may also belong to the Cybersecurity (cs.CY) sub-category, which deals with securing critical infrastructure.
